Sentencas: Crystal structure, thermal expansion coefficient; electrical conductivity and cathodic polarization of compositions in the system Sm0.5Sr0.5Co1-xFexO3-delta with 0 <= x <= 0.9 were studied as a function of Co/Fe ratio and temperature in air.
Titulo: A novel cathode material of iron-doping Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3 for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Two phases, an orthorhombic symmetry for 0 <= x <= 0.4 and a cubic symmetry for 0.5 <= x <= 0.9, were observed in samples Of Sm0.5Sr0.5Co1-xFe3-delta at room temperature.
Titulo: A novel cathode material of iron-doping Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3 for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The adjustment of thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) to electrolyte, which is one of the main problems of SSC, could be achieved to lower TEC values with more Fe substitution.
Titulo: A novel cathode material of iron-doping Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3 for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: High electrical conductivity above 100 S center dot cm(-1) at 800 degrees C was obtained for all specimens, so they could be good conductors as cathodes of IT-SOFC.
Titulo: A novel cathode material of iron-doping Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3 for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The polarization behavior of SSCF as a function of Fe content was evaluated by means of AC impedance using LSGM electrolyte.
Titulo: A novel cathode material of iron-doping Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3 for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: It is found that the Area Specific Resistance (ASR) of SSCF increases as the amount of substitution of Fe for Co increases.
Titulo: A novel cathode material of iron-doping Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3 for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: When the amount of Fe reaches to 0.4, the highest ASR is obtained and then the resistance starts decreasing.
Titulo: A novel cathode material of iron-doping Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3 for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The electrode with a composition of Su(0.5)Sr(0.5)Co(0.2)Fe(0.8)O(3-delta) shows high catalytic activity for oxygen reduction operating at temperature ranging from 700 to 800 degrees C.
Titulo: A novel cathode material of iron-doping Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3 for solid oxide fuel cell
